result.execSummary:
The defendant James Earl Davidson Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant James Earl Davidson in court with attorney Robert J Hampton.  Defendant James Earl Davidson in custody.  Micha Schwab appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant wants to change his plea.

As to both counts:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea. Judgment of conviction entered.
.
Sentencing continued....
.
  Sentencing proceeds.    Upon inquiry of the Court, State advises they have complied with victim notification. 
Statements by counsel and defendant.  

As to both counts:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 20 days at the House of Correction as to each count,  concurrent with each other but consecutive to case 15CM2891, with -0- days credit.
Defendant to pay all applicable costs, assessments and surcharges as to count 1, including the DV and DNA surcharges from bail on deposit.  If there is no posted bail the defendant is to pay the costs and surcharges within one year of today's date, failure to pay the costs and surcharges will result in a civil judgment.  As to count 2 the court found that the defendant is indigent and waived all costs and surcharges.
Court advises the defendant he may not possess a firearm; is to provide a DNA sample.  
Appeal rights given.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant James Earl Davidson in court with attorney Vladimir M. Gorokhovsky.  Defendant James Earl Davidson in custody.  Micha Schwab appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

In the middle of the plea hearing the defendant informed the court that his attorney told him that he should change his plea because if he takes the case to trial the court will give him the maximum sentence.  The court stopped the proceedings, removed defense counsel from the case and ordered the case adjourned for a status conference to allow the Public Defender's Office to appoint counsel.  Discovery was handed over to the district attorney in court.
